- Use semantic commit (e.g., feat, refactor, chore, style, docs ...)
- Add or change existing tests for each change you make
- Ensure each change have its own commit
- Once everything is implemented create a PR so that it contains two section:
  - "## Context" -> It highlights the change we want to introduce, keeping an high-level description. No need to be too detailed or technnical.
  - "## This PR" -> It describes the introduced changes, keeping an high-level description. No need to be too detailed or technnical.
